<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-04T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-04T19:00:00-05:00" n="382" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.918/10–445: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-04T19:00:00-05:00">October 4,
                                    1945—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1398. From Braden. Have just been informed by <hi rend="italic">Time</hi>
                            Magazine that while sales on newsstands in Buenos Aires of October 1st
                            issue have been permitted, distribution through post office (which
                            constitutes major portion of circulation) has been stopped by
                            Government.</p>
                        <p>This is in direct violation of Mexico City obligations and of agreement
                            Lomuto made with me on approximately June 13.<note n="34" xml:id="d382fn34">See telegram 1236, June 13, from Buenos Aires,
                                    <ref target="#pg_507">p. 507</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>Please protest this further violation. [Braden.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>